//===================================================================================
// README
//===================================================================================


To complete setup of the PourOver project...


CocoaPods
----------------------------------------
1. Run the CocoaPods install in the project folder.
2. To install CocoaPods on your Mac, see https://guides.cocoapods.org/using/getting-started.html
3. To run the installation, open the Terminal, 'cd' to the project directory (containing PourOver.xcodeproj), and run 'pod install'
----------------------------------------


libpd
----------------------------------------
1. Add libpd via GitHub to the xcworkspace. Do not use CocoaPods, since the Google Drive pod requires use_frameworks!, which is incompatible with the libpd pod.
2. For installation instructions, see https://github.com/libpd/libpd
3. If the linker fails to find 'PdAudioController.h', be sure to add the libpd directory (recursively) to PourOver >> Build Settings >> User Header Search Paths
----------------------------------------


[psr]
----------------------------------------
1. Copy the 'x_psr.c' file into the libpd project
2. Follow the instructions at the top of 'x_psr.c' to complete the installation of the external
----------------------------------------

